Social work as a profession based on values. Practical ethics and theories. Ethical considerations in social work. Values, human behaviour and responsibility. Conflict of values. Central dilemmas of value in social work. Principles of ethical practice. Code of ethics for social work. Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to create prerequisites for knowing and using the philosophical and ethical principles of social work as a value-based profession, and making decisions and socio-ethical analysis of society.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows the central values of social work and follows them in professional practice; 2) has the knowledge and skills to behave in conflict situations; 3) analyzes socio-ethical situations in society.
